&lt;p&gt;But how is it possible?&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;According to stories by Muhammad, initially, all Arabs were monotheists, and they were visiting Kaba for Hajj every year, and they were drinking water from Zamzam for centuries. How can then a tribe close and hide it, when thousands of Arabs knew exactly where it was situated (near Kaba) and drank water from it every year?&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Naturally, Islamic preachers have no answer to this. &lt;/p&gt;
